-- BOJ's Shirakawa: to continue powerful easing
-- 
-- Thu Mar 17, 2011 8:27pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/18/us-japan-economy-shirakawa-idUSTRE72H04820110318

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Bank of Japan Governor Masaaki Shirakawa said on Friday he expected joint G7 intervention will help stabilize the currency market. 

 "The BOJ expects cooperation with other countries will help stabilize the currency market," Shirakawa told reporter following a teleconference among the Group of Seven finance chiefs. Shirakawa also said the central bank will continue its powerful monetary easing and ample fund supplies to stabilize financial markets. At the meeting, the G7 countries agreed to jointly intervene in the currency market after the yen shot up to an all-time high on Wednesday. (Reporting by Rie Ishiguro; Editing by  Tomasz Janowski )